UNANSWERED LETTER
Tess Gallagher

Your silence is leaning towards judgement
Yesterday I bragged, writing to calm
my paranoid friend, that I never assumer
the worst when my pals don't write. Now
assuming the worst, I think what I must have
done, or not done. Surely some recognition
will brand the door of my hoyse, or
rich attention flutter down.

How natural, in silence, to credit delay
with intention, like the word oar
insisting on water. The need also to
advice the self around exaggeration,
i.e., "nobody loves me", because nothing is
coming back, and next to nothing, not
to act like a transistor radio left on into
the night, voices singing like an ear
baffled by the rain, or someone refused
because they think so.

Those others you loved elsewhere, you miss
what they haven't said. They belong
to some permission to go as more
than yourself, a clarity that adds you back
to all you cast off, as when
you want to be the good light of a lamp
scanning the firmanent, or rain- its pleasure
with an open boat.

So what is unanswered keeps you coming back
to yourself, telling you what you wanted
only when it didn't come, having now
to make up this difference.
Even moments you think empty, the world
doesn't stop speaking-the windshield
blurred suddenly by a sighting of gravestones,
before you are driver through the underpass

Hi world. This is from someone who is coming from Cramming-Math-World.

So, here's the thing. Monthsaries. Do people actually celebrate it? Is it sad when some guys just prefer not to?

My opinion: Not at all. I have NOOOOO IDEA WHY. ewan. perfectly logical?

kasi look at it this way: if you celebrate monthsaries, it's like showing people na "blah blah blah and I are together since blah blah time yada yada yada" and you tend to...duh, celebrate with all the this and that. but gets, if you guys really do like each other, you don't have to celebrate it every freaking month. tapos yung doing something special on your monthsary day. YOU CAN DO SOMETHING SPECIAL ANY DAY, cause every day is special when you're with that someone. gets? you don't need a date to proclaim your love. you can do it everyday. even the greeting also...you're proclaiming na rin na you've been with this person for blah blah months. well, for me it doesn't work that way. i don't think you have to count how long you guys are together. i mean yeah, the day you guys got together may be memorable but in the long run, you'd probably forget it. and i guess it doesn't matter as much cause as long as you're happy with each other, it doesn't matter how long you guys are or something. time won't dictate your relationship. what's important is what you have with the person. you don't have to proclaim it to the world. in the long run, hindi naman yung time na you guys got together ang babalikan niyo, it's the memories you have with the person.

and with that, here's to Math and the couple celebrating their monthsary. Happy first month. :)

change. it's evident this summer. 
change, it's been a long time since i've seen something big.

it's seen everywhere. in your friends. in your family.
true. change. is it good? is it bad?

in the relationships of the people around. 
how does it affect you? what makes you see? what makes you feel? how can someone stand on a ground like this.

friendships. love. summer romance, perhaps?
love. love is very overrated. friendships change. different levels. who knows where your friendship is moving? backwards? forwards? constant? never moving?

from looking afar, to being near.
being near? you know the phrase so close, yet so far? yeah, that one. being near? does it have to be near physically? emotionally? what is being near? or are you meant to just look from afar?

from being apart, to being together all the time.
like being stuck together on the hip. nothing's wrong with that, as long as you're happy. it can be the other way around too. being together all the time to being apart. at first, it's not a happy feeling. then, i guess you get used to it. but you don't know exactly when.

through the phone or online to seeing each other.
how things change. like technology. like science. like how everything else seem to be.

from school to the mall.
and much farther. sometimes, to the point that even our eyes can't see it anymore.

sadness to laughter.
how about the other way around? laughter to sadness. and depression. and hurt. and not wanting to feel that way anymore. how about confusion? laughter to confusion? laughter to being indifferent.

problems to solutions.
how about problems to more problems? how about problems to confrontation? confronting, does it give you a solution or more problems to your problems?

dreams to reality.
how about if dreams stay as dreams? because when it comes to reality, dream big, fall big, get hurt big. dreams shouldn't be mixed to reality. reality can hurt your dream.

having to losing.
letting go. having to losing is all about letting go. letting go until you learn to accept that you have to. that you can't do anything about it but move on.

being nothing to being someone.
is being someone worth it when you hurt other someones? is being someone worth it if you don't know who you are? is it being worth someone if you don't know if you can be a someone?

frowns to smiles.
smiles to frowns. it seems like a virus these days. when nothing good ever happens.

to having broken hearts.
and still continue to get your heart broken. because you never stop loving no matter how much the person can hurt you.

being ok to being happy.
happy? what is happiness exactly? what is happiness? smiling? being cheerful? people wear a mask of deceit. smile like there's nothing wrong. is perfection happiness? i don't think so. is satisfaction happiness? i don't think so. so, what is being happy?

closing a chapter and opening a new one.
this never ceases to fail. in everything you do, you always close a chapter and open a new one. do you reopen chapters? not the ones that are glued shut or refused to be read again. because no one wants history to repeat itself.

from bonding to falling apart.
can bonding cause you to fall apart? maybe you shouldn't bond more so you won't fall apart. then again, if you don't bond at all, then you will fall apart. so what is it? no matter what you do, you end up falling apart.

friendships and fights.
mix ups. right and wrong. making up. who knows what. does it make your friendship stronger or weaker. friendships cause people to fight and get hurt.

flow of emotions.
all the time. no one is stable on one emotion. then again. maybe they just can't feel anymore because that emotion is stuck in their heart.

thinking all the time.
thinking. sometimes, thinking is a way to get you to think again. and again. until you are confused. when you say something, your mind is halfway there because you want to believe what you are saying. you're not making people believe it. you're trying to make yourself believe it. and thinking about what you're supposed to believe in? happens all the time.

facing challenges.
no life has no challenge. whether it be physical, mental or emotional, there is a challenge that one must surpass, no matter how hard it is. the methods, you choose your own way.

to changing who you are.
change. it's inevitable. but you can't change who you are. because that's who you really are. that's what makes you YOU.

to how i see you. 
how i see you? it depends on how you see me. it's like something you can never reach. unreachable. who knows when i can see you. when i can see the real you. and when you can see the real me.

being someone different.
no one is alike. if everyone is alike, then no one will be different.

change.
all happening in one summer.
this summer.
summer of 2007.
 
how a lot of things can happen in a span of a year. change. who likes change? who likes being in a path when you don't know where the road is going? who likes not knowing how to deal with things and how things are going to be? who likes being in the dark.
 
i have a question. if everything changes, how do you know whether you should take a chance? and if you will be given another chance? if you would regret? if you would be happy? if you would get hurt?
 
the present. where everything goes by in a blink of an eye.

still counting backwards while the stars are falling down. it's one in a million the chances of feeling the way we do. we'll keep dancing wherever we go next.

LOVE? wahaha. topic! love is...BLIND? HAHAHA. totoo yan. people can be blinded by love.

pero love. love is when you take those risks. when you let go of yourself and allow yourself to accept other people. it's risky but it's worth if you love a person. love is a choice, it's not a feeling. it's something na pag binigay mo na, pwedeng maabuse or pwedeng mabigay in return. sometimes, love keeps a person going on..which is true in some cases pero sometimes it's hope na things will get better na keeps people going. 

love. love is something that cannot be bought. like seriously. don't even attempt. kasi masakit. sa sarili. haha. kahit i-deny mo pa yan, masakit.

love. love is something that you can deny yourself because you are afraid. oh yes, people are afraid of getting hurt. if you love a person, when that person hurts you, diba it's PAINFUL? sino ba hindi masasaktan kung hindi mo mahal yung tao? haha. manhid yun. pero then again, ang mga manhid, nagtatago lang ng feelings. so nasasaktan din sila. hindi lang natin alam, kasi akala natin manhid sila. hello. PEOPLE CAN FEEL PAIN. kasi it makes us real.

wahaha. napaka-negative ko naman about this topic. haha. 

kung sabihin ko man na love is blissful blah blah blah...hello, here comes the army of pain. woot. hindi pa tapos. you might have won the battle but lost the war. HAHAHAHA. nawawalan din ang tao ng pagmamahal. hello. pag nasaktan, it's hard for them to open up and all again because they don't want to get hurt again. who wants to get hurt anyway? happy happy dapat, dba? haha.

love is a virtue. tangina. oo. kung patience is a virtue, shouldn't love be? you learn to be patient slowly. ganun din sa love. kung may hate kang person, you got to love the person eventually. dahan dahan nga lang. minsan din, diba kailangan mo ng patience to wait. kung mahal mo talaga yung tao, that person is worth the wait.

LOVE. LOVE IS OVERRATED. tangina. :))

Iniibig kong mabuhay sa loob
Ng tulang mahal sa buhay
Upang takasan ang tunay na buhay

Ngunit maligalig ang espasyong
Naninikip sa katiyakan

Una kong itinapon palabas ang mga talinhaga 
Upang umalinas ang aking paghinga
Isa-isa silang naglahong parang bula
Mula sa aking mga kamay

Walang humpay akong nagbuhat
Araw-gabi, hanggang malubos
Ang mabibigat na salita liban sa akin

Doon ako mahimbing na namahinga
Sa lihim ng blankong pahina

watched a christina ricci movie titled penelope and all i can say is... I LOVE JAMES MC AVOY! hahaha, kind of reminds me of Diego Luna (but i love Diego Luna also!) It's about a girl named Penelope who is born with a curse. in order for the curse to be broken, she must find true love with one of her kind, which in her case is a blue-blood (rich people). then, there's this reporter who hires James Mc Avoy to get a picture of Penelope. to cut the story short, (and to spoil this movie) it is quite predictable with a lot of twists and it's so funny cause the moral of the story (supposedly) is to love yourself (which in the case of Penelope, she broke it herself), and it's not even really really visible until the end...the thin line connecting that moral to that story was the true love with one of her kind...and the love story between her and James Mc Avoy only bloomed in like 40 minutes of the film. and reese witherspoon was in a semi-cameo role, not really of importance, just shows penelope's first friend. and she doesn't realize that she loves james mc avoy until the end!!! but he was kinda hinting about it a little. so there. HAHAHA. watch penelope. light film, twisty and predictable. 

PS: my sister said she looked better before she transformed :))

Tonight I Can Write
Pablo Neruda

Tonight I can write the saddest lines

Write, for example, 'the night is shattered
and the stars are blue and shiver in the distance'

The night wind revolves in the sky and sings.

Tonight I can write the saddest lines.
I loved her, and sometimes she loved me too.

Through nights like this one I held her in my arms.
I kissed her again and again under the endless sky.

She loved me, and sometimes I loved her too.
How could one not love her great still eyes.

Tonight I can write the saddest lines.
To think that I do not have her. To feel that I have lost her.

To hear the immense night, still more immense without her.
And the verse falls to the soul like dew to the pasture.

What does it matter that my love could not keep her.
The night is starry and she is not with me.

This is all. In the distance someone is singing. In the distance
My soul is not satisfied that it has lost her.

My sight tries to find her as though to bring her closer.
My heart looks for her, and she is not with me.

The same night whitening the same trees
We, of that time, are no longer the same.

I no longer love her, that's certain, but how I loved her.
My voice tried to find the wind to touch her hearing.

Another's. She will be another's. Like my kisses before
Her voice, her bright body, her infinite eyes.

I no longer love her, that's certain, but maybe I love her.
Love is so short, forgetting is so long.

Because through nights like this one I held her in my arms
My soul is not satisfied that it has lost her.

Though this be the last pain she makes me suffer
and these the last verses I write for her.

****

Mannequin by Anonymous 

dressed up in latest trends
looking like everyone else

drenched in designer clothing
holding the newest purse
bodies dazzling in diamonds
displaying the latest footwear
air with foreign scent
newest colors released in the market

displayed somewhere rich and beautiful
a place where everyone wants to be in

clean and secured
carrying the richest of the rich
elites and the beautiful
socializing for connections
splurging to have the latest
popularity, fame

perfection in shape
flawless in essense
skin-wise

perfect body, perfect height
anorexic, bulimic
fashionable, celebrity
loved by few, idolized by all
beauty, perfection

faceless, emotionless
not one tear drop escaping from the eyes
not one smile playing on the lips
not one touch, no whisper of senseless words
no intelligence, no love
solid as a statue

wanting to be a clone of society
is it worth it? will happiness prevail?
will it impose something you're not?
as others begin to mold you
losing one's self
becoming a clone
becoming a mannequin

are you your own being or a being of someone else?
Mannequins. Inevitable
But your choice to make yourself avoid them.

you look around the ballroom. everyone is dressed up, and somehow, no one is noticing you. you see no familiar face. everyone is wearing a mask. everyone is ignoring you. you can't approach anyone. yet, the spotlight falls on the person in the middle of the ballroom and your face lit a smile. it was the only familiar face in the room. and that person is only waiting for someone, you. the person smiles at you and you smile back, happy to see him. he was holding a beautiful rose and he was waiting for you. you slowly approach him and he gives you the rose. you give him your sweetest smile then suddenly, a beautiful piece plays out of nowhere. he gives you a meaningful look then holds out his hand, asking you for a dance. you give him your sweet nod and takes his hand. he pulls you closer to him and he leads the dance. the spotlight just falls on the both of you, the lights are getting dim but you didn't notice. all you can see is him, his eyes looking lovingly at you, his warm smile. somehow, the entire room grew silent, as all eyes gazed on the two of you. you can notice everyone watching but didn't put a care with it, for the only one who really mattered is right there in front of you. he pulls you closer to him, just close enough to whisper the sweetest words you will hear. and you're wishing that night will never end. 

it's a cinderella story, right? where all that will happen in a dream. i mean, will that even happen in reality? when the guy of your dreams will just sweep you off your feet? this dream can be broken. seriously. 

he's been an hour late and you haven't heard a word. he hasn't called you and if you haven't insisted on seeing him, you wouldn't be meeting him. you have been waiting under the rain, by the park. you see people scurrying off to find shelter and you're waiting under your bright red umbrella. you take a look at your phone to see that he hasn't left a message or a call. since you are getting tired of waiting, you decided to go to a shop and wait there for him. as you walk to the shop, something by the street caught your eye. he was there, standing, waiting to cross the street. he was soaking wet and he was getting cold. you were about to wave at him when you saw another girl running towards him with an umbrella. she started to talk to him and you did nothing but stand there. as you were about to approach him, they have faced each other and somehow, they ended up in a liplock. you just stood there, staring and you looked away. tears start to flow from your eyes as you walked away, taking deep breaths along the way. 

that broke her entire dream, right? the entire dream of being happy. hey, you can say i watch too much tv. which is actually true. and i'll end this thing with another tv-like ending, i guess. or you want me to leave this hanging?
all im saying is that, the dream, can never become the reality. if you think your prince is going to sweep you off your feet like that, you're wrong. no one's love story is predictable. you can start by being friends, or enemies. it can start from a simple hello to long conversations. somehow, when you know it's meant to be, it is. and destiny can't be stopped. it can't be chosen. it's how you accept it. but when you find it, you can't let go of it. wanna know why? it's meant to be. no matter how much you try to forget, it is still gonna be a part of you. you might think that the person is the one, but what if the person's not? what if you have just been with that person for a long time and in the end you realize hindi pala siya. those things can happen. and you shouldn't call the other relationships a waste of time either, if your heart gets broken. because somehow, admit it or not, you learn something from it. and it can transform you to a better person. but as i said, it's your choice how you want to accept it. you can choose to move on, to love someone new or to completely isolate your heart from loving another person again, to play with your life, to use others as toys but you're not finding a replacement. you have to try to open up again. you can't have your heart out in the cold. somehow, you have to bring it near warmth. it might take time, or experience for your heart to feel that love for someone again but it's all part of the process of finding someone to love and learning. everyone must have at least loved someone more than their self. to some, they might have found it, but to the ones who are still looking, don't be afraid to try to love and don't hide when your heart gets broken. because it's all part of the process.

change. it's evident this summer. 
it's seen everywhere. in your friends. in your family.
in the relationships of the people around. 
friendships. love. summer romance, perhaps?
from looking afar, to being near.
from being apart, to being together all the time.
through the phone or online to seeing each other.
from school to the mall.
sadness to laughter.
problems to solutions.
dreams to reality.
having to losing.
being nothing to being someone.
frowns to smiles.
to having broken hearts.
being ok to being happy.
closing a chapter and opening a new one.
from bonding to falling apart.
friendships and fights.
flow of emotions.
thinking all the time.
facing challenges. now with someone.
to changing who you are.
to how i see you. 
being someone different.
change. 
all happening in one summer.
this summer.
summer of 2007.

miasma of cacophony. no matter how we try to ameliorate the quality of life it will never be consumate. this is very lucid and obfuscating reality. maybe it sounds gauche but the only way to survive in this raucous world is to be pious, because benisons are ophemeral. being cantakerous is inimical so as rapacity for wealth. paroxysm of laughter is the sangfroid of our mind.
